OL,3,CWorking age households predicted to be
OL,4,C#400 worse off on average in year ahead
OL,6,FThe Foundation, which is focused on
OL,7,Fimproving living standards for those
OL,8,Fon low-to-middle incomes, predicted
OL,9,Fthat working-age benefits will not
OL,10,Fkeep pace with inflation this year,
OL,11,Fadding that low-income renters will
OL,12,Falso be squeezed by a freeze on local
OL,13,Fhousing allowance.
OL,15,FHowever, it described national living
OL,16,Fwage increases as a "chink of light in
OL,17,Fan otherwise gloomy outlook".
