OL,3,CWorking age households predicted to be
OL,4,C#400 worse off on average in year ahead
OL,6,F"The typical household is now
OL,7,Fprojected to be #400 worse off this
OL,8,Ffinancial year, due to a combination
OL,9,Fof weakening earnings growth, rising
OL,10,Fhousing costs, taxes and bills, and
OL,11,Fbenefits struggling to outpace
OL,12,Finflation.
OL,14,F"As vulnerable households try to meet
OL,15,Fthese rising costs, the Government can
OL,16,Fhelp by bringing forward next year's
OL,17,Fwelcome universal credit boost to this
OL,18,FOctober."
